[Ruth Notes:]
- distinguishing between the thinking brain and the feeling brain 
- acknowledging that feeling brain is really driving the car 
- the thinking brain is trying to give directions but if the feeling part of us doesn't like the idea
- the feeling brain does what feels good and the thinking brain tries to justify it
- self awareness is understanding the feeling/emotional parts of ourselves well enough so the thinking brain can negotiate the tiny habits
